description:
In lichen_l2.c lichen_l2_input(), when HAVE_LICHEN_LINK is 0 (link layer disabled), there is a memcpy from input data to rx_ipv6_buf with a size check, but the check allows len == sizeof(rx_ipv6_buf) which is correct.

Location: firmware/bridge-zephyr/subsys/lichen/lichen_l2.c:510-516

Code:
- Line 510: if (len > sizeof(rx_ipv6_buf)) { ... return }
- Line 515: memcpy(rx_ipv6_buf, data, len);

This is actually correct - not a bug. The check on line 510 rejects oversized packets. Removing from findings.
